4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, the State Department of
6 Human Resources must ensure that foster parents have
7 certain rights.
8 This bill would provide that foster parents have
9 a right to be heard at any hearings concerning the
10 foster child and the right to submit a written report
11 to the court on the status and welfare of the foster
12 child.
13 This bill would provide that foster parents of
14 foster children who have been in the care of the
15 department for at least 15 months may intervene as a
16 matter of right in any proceeding relating to the
17 foster child.
18 This bill would also provide that the court may
19 deny the motion to intervene only if the court issues
20 findings articulating why the intervention would be a
21 detriment to the best interests of the child and would
22 interfere with the child's right to a timely and
23 permanent resolution of his or her case.
24
25
26 A BILL
27 TO BE ENTITLED
28 AN ACT
