AN ACT
HB571 INTRODUCED
29
30 Relating to foster parents; to amend Section 38-12A-2,
31 Code of Alabama 1975; to further provide for the rights of
32 foster parents; and to provide certain parents with the right
33 of intervention.
34 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
35 Section 1. Section 38-12A-2, Code of Alabama 1975, is
36 amended to read as follows:
37 "§38-12A-2
38 The Department of Human Resources shall ensure that
39 each foster parent shall have has all of the following rights:
40 (1) The right to be treated with dignity, respect,
41 trust, value, and consideration as a primary provider of
42 foster care and a member of the professional team caring for
43 foster children.
44 (2) The right to receive information concerning the
45 rights enumerated in this section.
46 (3) The right to a concise written explanation of their
47 role as foster parents in partnership with children and their
48 families, the department, and other providers,; the role of
49 the department,; and the rights and role of the members of the
50 birth family of a child in foster care.
51 (4) The right to training and support for the purpose
52 of improving skills in providing daily care and meeting the
53 needs of the child in foster care.
54 (5) The right to training, consultation, and assistance
55 in evaluating, identifying, and accessing services to meet
56 their needs related to their role as foster care providers.
