179 (25) For foster parents who have fostered a foster
180 child who has been in the custody of the department for at
181 least 15 months, the right to file to intervene as a party as
182 a matter of right in any legal proceeding involving the foster
183 child. The court shall grant a motion to intervene under this
184 subdivision, except for good cause shown. The court may deny
185 the motion to intervene if the court issues a timely written
186 order articulating findings that granting the foster parent's
187 motion to intervene would be detrimental to the child's best
188 interests and would interfere with the foster child's right to
189 a timely and permanent resolution to the case. Foster parents
190 with the right to intervene under this subdivision do not need
191 the consent of the Department of Human Resources in order to
192 file a motion to intervene, and shall be entitled to file such
193 a motion without threat of reprisal for acting on good cause.
194 This subdivision does not entitle a foster parent to
195 court-appointed counsel."
